ive code may be more susceptible to buffer overflows and other attacks.\r\nNative code is unprotected by the security features enforced by the runtime environment, such as strong typing and array bounds checking.</p>\r\n<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\nclass Echo {\r\n    public native void runEcho(); // Noncompliant\r\n    static {\r\n        System.loadLibrary(\"echo\");\r\n    }\r\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\r\n        new Echo().runEcho();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n<pre>\r\nclass Echo {\r\n    private native void runEcho(); // Noncompliant - 'runEcho()' is a private member, but more than one place to invoke a method.\r\n    static {\r\n        System.loadLibrary(\"echo\");\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public void foo() {\r\n        ...\r\n        runEcho();\r\n        ...\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public void bar() {\r\n        ...\r\n        runEcho();\r\n        ...\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\r\n        new Echo().runEcho();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>\r\n<pre>\r\nclass Echo {\r\n    private native void runEcho();\r\n    static {\r\n        System.loadLibrary(\"echo\");\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // Implement error handling around the JNI call.\r\n    public void wrapper() {\r\n        ...\r\n        runEcho();\r\n        ...\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public void bar() {\r\n        ...\r\n        wrapper();  // invoked wrappers of native methods.\r\n        ...\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\r\n        new Echo().wrapper();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n<h2>See</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li> <a href=\"https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/111.html\">CWE-111</a> - Direct Use of Unsafe JNI </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n","category":0,"severity":4,"templateIds":null,"semanticAnalysis":false,"selected":true},{"id":1698,"name":"STJ0002","title":"Public Data Assigned to Private Array-Typed Field","description":"<p>Assigning public data to a private array is equivalent to giving public ac